<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="879" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d879">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 704.9312/5.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-27"><hi rend="italic">May 27,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>If the Mexican Government has no objections the consular agent at Torreón
                            may be instructed to extend his informal good offices in behalf of Mr.
                            Woo Lam Po.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>